{
  "text": "A possible additional route of transmission is suggested by the observed oral shedding of WNV-infected`Amakihi. [CITATION_1] demonstrated experimental per os transmission in House Sparrows by administering an aqueous solution containing 10 7.4 PFU of WNV. We detected similar concentrations of virus in oral swabs from infected`Amakihi, and it is conceivable that infected individuals might directly transmit WNV by regurgitating food for nestlings or indirectly transmit to other birds through nectar feeding.",
